library.description:
TAsync is a javascript module to help the development of asynchronous code. It can be both used with node.js or directly in the browser. TAsync can be characterized as a future/promise library with some unique features:

follows stack traces across asynchronous calls,
real and future values can be mixed freely,
execution can be throttled in logical execution time.
library.name: TAsync
